rComments: I disliked the format of the class since most of the assignments were based on group work. It was hard to get an A in this class as the prof has high expectations. He has a sense of humour, but I found the material hard to grasp.

All I learned in this class was that Toby works for the government, and apparently does something there related to communications planning. He didn't even write the final exam - he just downloaded it from another university website. Avoid this class if you intend to learn anything.

For a friday night class you would think he would try to make things interesting...Every class people were falling asleep. 1 group project and 1 final paper. No clear direction on how to complete either...Hard marker. Doesn't reply to emails in timely manner-hardly answers your questions...AVOID.

A generous person who allows for the technical errors that can occur in a video production class. I found him a hard marker on exams though.  Show up for every class (takes attendance).  Brings industry experience to the table.
